1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,410
Case number one.
2
00:00:01,600 --> 00:00:04,610
Why G.N. hasn't married.
3
00:00:05,201 --> 00:00:10,850
Mr. G.N. is now in his late thirties, is well-educated, works as an accountant,
4
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:12,850
and lives alone in Chicago.
5
00:00:13,201 --> 00:00:15,891
G.N.'s big desire is to get married.
6
00:00:16,081 --> 00:00:20,850
He wants love, companionship, a home, children, the works.
7
00:00:21,201 --> 00:00:23,490
G.N. has been close to marriage.
8
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:26,131
Once he was only one day away.
9
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:32,450
But each time he has been near marriage, he discovers something wrong with the girl he's about to marry.
10
00:00:32,721 --> 00:00:36,050
Just in time before I made an awful mistake.
11
00:00:36,560 --> 00:00:38,610
One instance stands out.
12
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:43,730
Two years ago, Jian thought he finally had met just the right girl.
13
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:46,771
She was attractive, pleasant, intelligent.
14
00:00:46,961 --> 00:00:51,571
But Jian had to be absolutely sure that marriage was the right thing.
15
00:00:51,841 --> 00:00:59,410
As they were discussing marriage plans one evening, the future Mrs. Jian made a few remarks that bothered Jian.
16
00:00:59,920 --> 00:01:09,971
So, to make certain he was marrying the right girl, G.N. drew up a four-page document of stipulations she was to agree to before they got married.
17
00:01:10,321 --> 00:01:17,170
The document, neatly typed and looking very legal, covered every segment of living G.N. could think of.
18
00:01:17,521 --> 00:01:22,931
There was one section on religion, what church they would go to, how often they would attend,
19
00:01:23,040 --> 00:01:24,610
how much they would donate.
20
00:01:24,881 --> 00:01:28,610
Another section covered children, how many and when.
21
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:36,371
In detail, G.N. outlined the kind of friends they would have, his future wife's employment status,
22
00:01:36,401 --> 00:01:39,651
where they would live, how their income would be spent.
23
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:48,131
To finish the document, G.N. devoted half a page to listing specific habits the girl must break or must acquire.
24
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:53,971
This covered such habits as smoking, drinking, makeup, entertainment, and so on.
25
00:01:54,800 --> 00:02:00,610
When Jian's prospective bride reviewed his ultimatum, she did what you would expect.
26
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:06,531
She sent it back with a note saying, the usual marriage clause, for better or for worse,
27
00:02:06,641 --> 00:02:10,290
is good enough for everyone else, and it's good enough for me.
28
00:02:10,480 --> 00:02:12,371
The whole thing is off.
29
00:02:13,281 --> 00:02:20,771
As Jian was relating his experience to me, he said worriedly, now what was so wrong in writing out this agreement?
30
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:23,251
After all, marriage is a big step.
31
00:02:23,281 --> 00:02:25,011
You can't be too careful.
32
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,331
But Jian was wrong.
33
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:30,211
You can be too careful, too cautious.
34
00:02:30,321 --> 00:02:35,891
Not only in planning a marriage, but in planning anything in the world where things get done.
35
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:38,371
The standards can be too high.
36
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:45,971
Jian's approach to marriage was very much like his approach to his work, his savings, his friendships, everything else.
37
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:53,490
The test of a successful person is not an ability to eliminate all problems before they arise,
38
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:57,410
but to meet and work out difficulties when they do arise.
39
00:02:57,761 --> 00:03:05,091
We must be willing to make an intelligent compromise with perfection, lest we wait forever before taking action.
40
00:03:05,281 --> 00:03:09,410
It's still good advice to cross bridges as we come to them.
41
00:03:10,401 --> 00:03:11,730
Case number two.
